Sentencas: The production and optimisation of screen printing (SP) pastes containing La(0.58)Sr(0.42)Co(0.21)Fe(0.79)O(3-delta) and La(0.61)Sr(0.41)Co(0.19)Fe(0.79)O(3-delta) (LSCF) were investigated.
Titulo: The Rheology of Stabilised Lanthanum Strontium Cobaltite Ferrite Nanopowders in Organic Medium Applicable as Screen Printed SOFC Cathode Layers

Sentencas: The application of these nanopowders is supposed to improve the cathode's microstructure and increase its mechanical strength.
Titulo: The Rheology of Stabilised Lanthanum Strontium Cobaltite Ferrite Nanopowders in Organic Medium Applicable as Screen Printed SOFC Cathode Layers

Sentencas: Thirty seven pastes containing LSCF were carried out with variation in binders, dispersants and different particle size distribution.
Titulo: The Rheology of Stabilised Lanthanum Strontium Cobaltite Ferrite Nanopowders in Organic Medium Applicable as Screen Printed SOFC Cathode Layers

Sentencas: The rheological behaviour of these pastes was investigated.
Titulo: The Rheology of Stabilised Lanthanum Strontium Cobaltite Ferrite Nanopowders in Organic Medium Applicable as Screen Printed SOFC Cathode Layers

Sentencas: It was found that commercially available dispersant Solsperse 3000 resulted in the best suspension stability, achieving almost 55 times lower viscosity value for pastes containing 20 vol.-%, than pastes without any dispersants.
Titulo: The Rheology of Stabilised Lanthanum Strontium Cobaltite Ferrite Nanopowders in Organic Medium Applicable as Screen Printed SOFC Cathode Layers

Sentencas: The shear thinning behaviour was found to be favourable for the LSCF cathode deposition.
Titulo: The Rheology of Stabilised Lanthanum Strontium Cobaltite Ferrite Nanopowders in Organic Medium Applicable as Screen Printed SOFC Cathode Layers

Sentencas: A cathode made from the mixture of nano and submicron powder exhibits a polarisation resistance as low as 0.76 Omega cm(2) at 592 degrees C.
Titulo: The Rheology of Stabilised Lanthanum Strontium Cobaltite Ferrite Nanopowders in Organic Medium Applicable as Screen Printed SOFC Cathode Layers
